    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">659.116Auto/4</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Owen</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 108</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-22">January 22,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madam</hi>: I enclose copies, as listed, of recent
                    correspondence with Mr. Pyke Johnson, Vice President of the Automobile
                    Manufacturers Association, Washington, D. C.,<note n="2" xml:id="d139fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> in regard to the restriction of imports of American
                    automobiles into Denmark.</p>
                <p>You are requested to do whatever you feel will be helpful in bringing about a
                    lessening of the import restrictions on American products.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis B. Sayre</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
